-- First Bank of Nigeria to Expand in Kenya, Ghana, Congo, Angola Next Year
-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-10-04T12:44:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/first-bank-of-nigeria-to-expand-in-kenya-ghana-congo-angola-next-year.html
First Bank of Nigeria Plc plans to
start expanding in Kenya, Ghana, Democratic Republic of Congo
and Angola next year, said Oluyemisi Lanre-Phillips, head of
investor relations.  The company also plans to open representative offices in
Dubai and New York, Lanre-Phillips said in a speech in
Johannesburg today. First Bank wants to expand financial
services outside of banking internationally in 2013, Lanre-
Phillips said. The lenderâ€™s joint venture with Sanlam Ltd., a
South African insurer, should start this quarter, Lanre-Phillips
